properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 3:14AM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED ON SUNDAY...

.A low pressure system will track from the Plain towards southern
Wisconsin on Sunday. Snow will spread across the area from
southwest to northeast during the morning, continue through
afternoon, and then end during the evening.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches.

* WHERE...Lincoln and Marathon Counties.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow is expected from late
morning into early afternoon, which will create much lower
visibility along with slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
